net.zer0bandwidth.android.lib.util

Interface StringComparator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<java.lang.String>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    JavaStringComparator, LexicalStringComparator, StringComparator.Base

    public interface StringComparator
extends java.util.Comparator<java.lang.String>
    There might be lots of ways to compare strings. There are at least two of them just in this library. Also, I get pretty crossed up as to how the value returned by a comparator works. So here's an interface with some handy semantic constants for derpy developers like myself.
    Since:
    zer0bandwidth-net/android 0.2.1 (#56)
